{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772211796,"nonce":"TNqF4R+KtO2MRh1qgmO+xDXS6j8=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87uiV18","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/315","origin":"github"},"title":"Prevent plan-task draft PRs from being confused with issues","message":"## Problem\n\nWhen `plan-task` creates a draft PR for plan review, the PR number enters the\nsame namespace as issues. A subsequent agent session (or even the same session\nafter context compression) can mistake the **PR number** for an **issue number**,\ncreating a second worktree and branch for the PR number instead of the original\nissue.\n\nThis happened with #293:\n\n1. Issue **#293** filed: \"Document env.sh requirement for per-package testing\"\n2. `plan-task` created `feature/issue-293` with a plan commit, then opened\n   **PR #312** (draft) with the plan as the body\n3. A new session saw #312, treated it as the issue to implement, created\n   `feature/issue-312`, and opened **PR #313** with `Closes #312`\n4. The original **#293** was orphaned — never referenced by the implementation PR\n\n### Impact\n\n- Issue-to-PR traceability is broken\n- The original issue doesn't auto-close on merge\n- Extra worktrees / branches / PRs clutter the repo\n- Human has to manually untangle the references\n\n## Analysis: Draft PR pros and cons\n\n### Pros of plan-as-draft-PR (current approach)\n\n- **Review tooling**: Copilot and human reviewers can comment inline on the plan\n  using GitHub's PR review UI\n- **Visibility**: Draft PRs show up in the PR list, making in-flight plans\n  discoverable\n- **Transition**: The draft PR can be promoted to the implementation PR — no\n  need to open a second PR after implementation\n\n### Cons\n\n- **Number collision**: The draft PR gets a number in the issue namespace,\n  which agents confuse with the issue number — this is the root cause of this bug\n- **Stale drafts**: If the plan is revised or the approach changes, the draft PR\n  body drifts from the actual plan file in `.agent/work-plans/`\n- **Double PR**: In practice, agents open a *new* PR for implementation anyway\n  (as happened here), so the \"promote the draft\" benefit is unrealized\n\n## Proposed approach\n\nKeep the draft PR (the review-tooling benefit is real), but add safeguards\nagainst number confusion:\n\n1. **Title prefix**: Draft plan PRs should use a `[PLAN]` prefix in the title\n   (e.g., `[PLAN] Document env.sh requirement...`) so they are visually\n   distinct from implementation PRs.\n\n2. **Plan body must reference the source issue prominently**: The draft PR body\n   should start with `Plan for #\u003cN\u003e` (linking back to the original issue), not\n   just `Closes #\u003cN\u003e`. This makes the relationship obvious.\n\n3. **Implementation guard**: Before creating a worktree or branch, agents should\n   verify the target number is an issue (not a PR). The `worktree_create.sh`\n   script could add a check:\n   ```bash\n   # Reject if the number is a PR, not an issue\n   if gh pr view \"$ISSUE_NUM\" --json number \u0026\u003e/dev/null 2\u003e\u00261; then\n     echo \"Error: #$ISSUE_NUM is a pull request, not an issue.\"\n     exit 1\n   fi\n   ```\n\n4. **`plan-task` should reuse the worktree's draft PR**: If `worktree_create.sh\n   --plan-file` already created a draft PR, `plan-task` step 6 should detect it\n   and update the existing PR body rather than creating a second one.\n\n## Files likely affected\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `.claude/skills/plan-task/SKILL.md` | Add `[PLAN]` prefix, prominent issue link, detect existing draft PR |\n| `.agent/scripts/worktree_create.sh` | Add issue-vs-PR guard; add `[PLAN]` prefix to draft PR title |\n| `AGENTS.md` | Note that plan PRs use `[PLAN]` prefix (if mentioned in workflow docs) |\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] Draft plan PRs have a `[PLAN]` title prefix\n- [ ] Draft plan PR body starts with a prominent link to the source issue\n- [ ] `worktree_create.sh` refuses to create a worktree for a PR number\n- [ ] `plan-task` detects and reuses an existing draft PR on the same branch\n- [ ] No new number-confusion incidents in subsequent plan-task runs\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null}]}